        <div class="InsideBlock" id="HOS">
            <div class="InsideBlockBody">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-lg-7">
                        <p>
                            Let me begin by congratulating each one of you for choosing MLSI as a school for your child.
                            It is with great pride and excitement that I share this introduction to you as the Head of School of MLSI. I am honoured to have the opportunity to lead a school with such a rich tradition of education!

                        </p>
                        <p>
                            I have been dedicated to the field of education for more than 24 years.
                            As an educator I am very passionate about IB education and have a rich experience of working with the IB in many roles.
                            I look forward to partnering with you to provide our students with a rigorous, engaging, and high-quality school experience. Parents are every child's first teacher and I believe that by working together, we can make sure your child's social, emotional, and academic needs are met.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            I will be working closely with the Management and the staff to guarantee that all of our students are intellectually challenged. Our main aim is to create global citizens who will become leaders for tommorow.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            As your Head of School, it is important to me that everyone who steps through our doors-teachers, students, and parents-are excited to be here! This attitude enables us to meet the challenges of academic excellence in a positive, fun, and nurturing environment. My door is always open and I welcome your input throughout the school year. Please feel free to call or email me to discuss any concerns, or ideas you would like to share; our continued success is dependent on your feedback.
                            I look forward to working with you as a team to help each student at MLSI meet their goals and become successful learners.

                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-5">
                        <div class="AcademicTeamPhoto">
                            <a href="~/Images/Priya-Anand.jpg" data-fancybox>
                                <img src="~/Images/Priya-Anand.jpg" alt="" />
                            </a>
                            <h4>Priya Anand</h4>
                            <h5>
                                Head of School
                            </h5>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="InsideBlock" id="PYPCoordinator">
            <div class="InsideBlockBody">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-lg-5">
                        <div class="AcademicTeamPhoto">
                            <a href="~/Images/Chandrani.jpg" data-fancybox>
                                <img src="~/Images/Chandrani.jpg" alt="" />
                            </a>
                            <h4>Ms. Chandrani Banerjee</h4>
                            <h5>
                               PYP Coordinator
                            </h5>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-7">
                      <p>
                        It is with immense enthusiasm that I embark on this educational journey
                        alongside you and your children.
                      </p>
                      <p>
                        Our vision for education is firmly rooted in the principles of the International Baccalaureate (IB) Primary Years Programme. We are dedicated to providing a
                        learning environment that encourages holistic development, critical thinking, and global awareness. It is my goal to create a dynamic space where your children
                        can thrive academically, emotionally, and socially.
                      </p>
                      <p>
                        As the PYP Coordinator, my role goes beyond being an educator. We are here to be a partner in your child's educational journey, working hand in hand with our
                        talented team of educators to design a curriculum that empowers students to become lifelong learners. Our focus is not just on academic success, but on nurturing
                        students who are confident, compassionate, and capable of embracing the challenges that lie ahead.
                      </p>
                      <p>
                        We are a firm believer in the power of collaboration between parents, educators, and students. We see parents as our invaluable allies in ensuring your child's
                        growth and success. We invite you to be active participants in your child's education, to engage in meaningful conversations, and to join us in fostering an
                        environment where curiosity is celebrated, questions are encouraged, and learning is a shared adventure. An integral part of this journey is the PYP Exhibition -
                        a culmination of your child's exploration, creativity, and learning. It's a moment where their academic and personal growth shine, as they take ownership of
                        their projects and present them to the community. Your involvement and support during this event can make a significant difference in your child's confidence
                        and overall experience.
                      </p>
                      <p>
                        With your support and our collective efforts, we can create an educational experience that prepares our students not only for academic excellence but also for
                        a future where they can make meaningful contributions to their communities and the world at large. I am excited to meet each one of you, to collaborate closely,
                        and to witness the remarkable growth of our children as they embark on this exciting journey through the MLSI PYP program.
                      </p>
                    </div>                    
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="InsideBlock" id="AssociatePYPCoordinator">
