                            </a>
                            <h4>Ms.Saolee Roy</h4>
                            <h5>
                               DP Coordinator
                            </h5>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-7">
                      <p>
                        The Diploma programme was introduced at Mount Litera School International in 2018 and received its authorization in 2019. Over the years, the DP team has expanded significantly.
                        The school offers a diverse range of DP subjects, enabling students to tailor their choices based on their interests. For instance, in Group 3, subjects like Business Management,
                        Economics, History, Psychology, and Environmental System and Societies are available. In Group 4, options include Biology, Chemistry, Physics, Computer Science, Sports Exercise and
                        Health Science, Design Technology, and Environmental System and Societies. This comprehensive selection of subjects at MSI empowers students to choose the ones aligning with their
                        college aspirations. Our accomplished team of experienced teachers, many of whom are also IB examiners, ensures students are well-prepared for the exams, contributing to our impressive 100% DP results.
                      </p>
                      <p>
                        The DP program at our school is holistic, integrating academic studies with Core subjects such as Theory of Knowledge, Extended Essay, and Creativity, Activity, and Service.
                        Our students excel in these Core components, evident from the remarkable 33.33% achieving a perfect 3 points in the 2023 DP examination. This achievement reflects their adeptness
                        in applying approaches to learning skills. Engaging in meaningful service activities is a cornerstone of our DP program. Students participate in endeavors like medical camps in
                        rural Maharashtra, blood donation drives, year-long teaching programs, and book donation initiatives. Furthermore, students have access to extracurricular activities beyond teaching
                        hours, fostering a balanced growth.
                      </p>
                      <p>
                        Numerous leadership opportunities are available, including positions in the Student Council, Rotaract and Interact clubs, and event organization. This enables students to refine their
                        leadership abilities. Our exceptional career counseling team assists students throughout the college admission process, from profile building to university fairs and applications,
                        ensuring our students secure placements in prestigious institutions worldwide.
                      </p>
                      <p>
                        Guided by the IB's ethos, we cultivate internationally minded students dedicated to creating a harmonious world. Over my 15 years of experience, I've witnessed the remarkable transformation
                        of IB students into capable young adults who assume responsibility for their lives with grace. As the Diploma Programme Coordinator, I extend a warm invitation to students to join us for a
                        life-transforming experience at MLSI.
                      </p>
                    </div>                    
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

